<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-6109] &lt;to/&gt; step in a &lt;doCatch/&gt; block runs when the &lt;doTry/&gt; tag is closed in the wrong place</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6109</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Example route:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;doTry&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;to ... &amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/doTry&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;doCatch&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;exception&amp;gt;java.lang.Exception&amp;lt;/exception&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;to uri=&quot;log.... &quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/doCatch&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The &amp;lt;to uri=&quot;log...&quot;/&amp;gt; line will execute every time, regardless if there is an exception or not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe the preferred behavior would be that the route should fails to load/validate.  Alternatively, the &amp;lt;to uri=&quot;log..&quot; /&amp;gt; should not run when there is not an exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows dev&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
