                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13589205" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2013 05:23:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The doCatch should be &lt;b&gt;inside&lt;/b&gt; the doTry, as documented in its documentation: &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.apache.org/try-catch-finally.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.apache.org/try-catch-finally.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13589244" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2013 06:32:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On 2nd though lets add validation to the Camel model so we can detect the mis configuration of having doCatch outside doTry etc. Then we can tell the end user about this mis configuration so they can fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13589568" author="mattrpav" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2013 14:38:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Claus. The syntax check to alert users to the incorrect configuration was what I was hoping for. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It can be a little confusing since for users coming from a plain Java coding background. When programming plain Java code the try {} closes before the catch {} opens.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
